  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-06-12",
    "date": "2003-08-27T19:56:43Z",
    "text": "Secure Annuity Income for Life Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income a percentage of lifetime annuity payments from a qualified trust to a qualified distributee. Provides for recapture and taxation of payments that are modified (other than by death or disability) so as to not qualify as lifetime annuity payments.\n\nApplies such exclusion to: (1) section 403(a) plans (employee annuities); (2) section 403(b) plans (public schools and certain tax exempt organizations); (3) section 408 plans (individual retirement accounts); and (4) section 457 plans (deferred compensation plans for State and local governments and tax-exempt organizations).\n\nDefines: (1) \"lifetime annuity payment\"; and (2) \"qualified distributee.\""
  },
